1. Prerequisites
Python 3.x installed on your system.
OpenWeather API key (sign up for a free account here).

2. Clone the Repository
Clone this project to your local machine:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/uk-weather-app.git
cd uk-weather-app

3. Install Required Libraries
Install Flask and Requests:

bash
Copy code
pip install flask requests

4. Set Your API Key
Replace API_KEY in the app.py file with your OpenWeather API key:

python
Copy code
API_KEY = "your_openweather_api_key"
5. Run the App
Run the Flask app:

bash
Copy code
python app.py
The app will start on http://127.0.0.1:5000/. Open this link in your browser.
